,Recommended,254440,8560935,"Posted: 4 January, 2014",all,<TVB>altabiscuit,"This game is billiards in its purest form.  The physics work well, the game is accessible for anyone to pick up and play while still having advanced shots for tricksters, and the online play works well.I use a keyboard and mouse for controls but I've been told by friends who use a 360 controller that it works fine there too.  The controls take a little getting used to and because of this I highly recommend playing through the tutorial.  It took me about an hour to get used to doing trick shots.  If trick shots are becoming too easy then I recommend turning up the difficulty on the aiming aid.There are a few other things I'd like to point out though it does not change my recommendation.First, some of the game modes like Golf aren't available in online play for some reason.  A few game modes such as Snooker or Cutthroat are not in the game either which is disappointing.  Snooker is being added in a future patch but at the time of this review it is not there.  Tournament mode doesn't seem to work either, I can't seem to get more than two people into a lobby.  An improved lobby system would be nice.  Allowing 3 people into a lobby would also be nice where one person can watch and then play the winner/loser or something or allows 3 players like Cutthroat.The replay system doesn't seem to work right either.  I haven't been able to save any replays because the controls on the system are not responsive or the binded keys are labeled incorrectly.Despite my minor complaints about the game, this is still a faithful recreation of billiards.  More updates are coming in the future and may fix/add the features I've mentioned.TL;DR version:  If you enjoy billiards, buy this game.EDIT:  As of the 1/8/2013 patch, the replay system works properly and the controls are responsive."
