,Recommended,254440,11499845,"Posted: 31 July, 2014",all,CasuallyJesus,"I can rarely say i've spent 8+ Hours enjoying something i only paid £1.04 for.I'm not usually a player of simulation games, but this game is very enjoyable. Potting is so satisfying and once you start completing skillshots, it's enough to make a grown man make girlish squeals of pleasure.Pros- Very easy to ""pick up & play"" the tutorials are well done, but are OPTIONAL, so you can do them whenever you feel like, if at all and repeatable, so you can brush up on certain types of shots if you are having difficulty.- All of the things that make this more game than simulation can be turned off or not used. Those who want a challenge don't have to have aiming lines or use flashbacks.- Loads of unlockable customisation options, unlike certain simulators where to get a new table or cues (or trains or pinballs) you have to get your wallet out, 95+% of the customisation options are unlockable by beating different challenges or tours.- Each match in a tour comes with 2 challenges that require you to win the match in certain ways, such as using a particular shot or getting a high score, etc, giving completionists more to achieve.- Scrolling the mouse back & forth to control the cue is enjoyable- The graphics are amazing. Bearing in mind i'm playing this on a laptop, it looks beautiful. I would go as far as saying this is the best looking game i've run on this, with no framerate drops.Cons- The menu can occasionally get fiddly.- Sometimes, when trying to aim the cue with the middle-mouse-button, the camera pans up instead.- Extremely rare crashes. Had 2 so far, but i'm unsure if that's something to do with my hardware to be honest.Seriously, just look through the rest of the reviews. There are HUNDREDS of reviews, all positive, some are casual players, some are hardcore simulation players, all of them love it. Even when this game isn't on sale, it is totally worth the full asking price. If you're even slightly interested in this game, pick it up, you won't be disappointed."
