,Recommended,254440,17975611,"Posted: 10 September, 2015",all,Shinigami,"Very nice pool game, with main limitation being aim assist only calculating trajectories till the first collision. After the first collision, no collisions are taken into account. This means you can't tell how the balls will move if you hit one ball with another (unless you spend 1000s of hours practicing).Game has normal ""tournament"" mode, where you play against various AI players and collect ""stars"" for completing challenges, as well as ""endurance"" mode, where balls are continiously dropped on the field, and an online multiplayer, as well as ""versus AI"" mode, tricks mode (where you build levels and try to perform some sort of insanity). There could be more, but I mostly play endurance.Graphics is a bit too glossy with all the extra (unneeded, in my personal opinion) reflections and shines. Sound is nice, especially balls hitting other balls. Music is OK, but selection is quite limited, you'll be listening to same tunes over time.Overall, I like the game. It has its flaws, but its quite relaxing."
