,Recommended,254440,7634972,"Posted: 11 November, 2013",all,arleas,"The game is very shiny, the game physics feel like they're very good.   It's got 8-ball, 9-ball, Straight pool, 3 Ball, Rotation, Speed pool and they're going to add more.The AI seems kinda bland, like all the AI opponents are just ""I'll take 3 good shots and then screw up on purpose"".  The opponents don't talk to you, and heck, you don't even see them walk around the table or anything.  I feel like they could have gone that extra mile to make the opponents in game seem more lively or personable.There's also options for various kinds of customizations.  You have table decals (which range from the mildly distracting to the highly annoying), and decorative balls (all of which are EXTREMELY SHINY!).  You can even customize your pool cue though you'll barely notice that in game.  Finally you can change your game location from a huge room with a view, to a huge room with a view at night, and then to another room without that great of a view...  Again, I feel like they could have made the locations a bit more interesting instead of looking like you're inside a museum.There's an upcoming ""Trick shot"" mode which may be amusing to play around with, and also snooker is promised as DLC (whether that's worth the extra price or not remains to be seen).The music is a bit too ""jazzy"" or ""technoish"" for my tastes but you can turn the volume down.  It would be nice if each location had its own soundtrack (to add more personality to each place) but that could be asking for too much.  It would also be nice if you could tell the game your music folder location and let it play songs from that randomly.All in all though, this is worth the full price, and if it's on sale, buy it now... I've already gotten my money's worth out of it."
