,Recommended,254440,11089878,"Posted: 5 July, 2014",all,theinvincible316,"If you're looking for a pool game on Steam, look no further. This is the most graphically, physically, and stylistically impressive pool game I've ever played, and I've been playing them for almost my whole life (going all the way back to Side Pocket on the NES.) The balls, rails and pockets behave just as they would on a real pool table. And there are a bunch of different ways to play, thanks to many diverse mini-games. There's a great training mode too, so even anyone who has never played pool before can pull off trick shots like a master. There's nothing more satisfying than seeing your perfectly aimed jump shot in slow motion as it knocks the target ball in the pocket. It's fun, it's calming, it's everything a great pool game should be. And I recommend it."
