,Recommended,254440,12297949,"Posted: 30 September, 2014",all,[LUC] BrainOfJ83,"There's a lot of good, free pool games on websites for you to play, so why should you even care about Pool Nation? Because if you like pool-gamesyou'll have to buy a waterproof computeryou really should care about it!Visually it's quite the looker... I'm not gonna go into the whole ""shiny balls"" discussion, but it is a good looking game. The physics are also spot on, and you can have a little bit more of finesse in your shots in comparison to most free web-based pool-games. There are a handful of game modes including your classics like 8ball and 9ball. The only thing missing is snooker, which isn't a pool-game by itself but it would've been fun to have it included.The single player campaign is fun with ""missions"" for every match that'll give you bonuses and unlocks if you manage to achieve them. Also, of course, there's online multiplayer.The only negative thing I can come to think of is that the port (it was originally released on console) didn't really manage to get the ""select ball and pocket""-mechanic to work with a mouse-and-keyboard-setup which feels kinda strange since it should be easier with a mouse than with a controller. You'll get past that but at first it gets really frustrating if you want to pocket the ball in another pocket than what the game assumes.With that said there's just one question you need to ask yourself; do I want to play pool on my computer? If the answer is ""yes"" then Pool Nation is the game for you. If the answer is ""no""... go get that waterproof PC."
