76561198059672439,Recommended,254440,12334999,"Posted: 3 October, 2014",all,IIEx~M43hin4,"Realistic game of pool, sounds great and the physics are nice.There's different camera views, you have a top down mode for when you need to look at the entire table for extreme accuracy, and a first-person? (not sure what to call it) mode and it feels great to play in, like you're really at a pool table playing.They even have slow-mo cams that zoom in to the ball when you've shot one in(only happens once in a while so it's not annoying and you can skip it if you want by pressing the button for skipping; you can even choose to skip the turns the npc takes when you want to play against them).Singleplayer has different modes,and you can play against npcs in several types of games (while sometimes unlocking different designs for the cue, ball, or the table as rewards for certain things).There's 'free mode' where you can just play by yourself without a limit (if you just want to shoot while relaxing or try out certain moves).There's also an endurance mode, which is like free mode (the by yourself without npc aspect), but is timed or rather the goal is to shoot as many balls in as you can, as fast and accurate as you can before too many extra balls get added to the table.And they have a tutorial mode where you can learn how to play and learn advanced tricks.You can turn the guiding 'lines' completely off, for people who want to play real-world style;they're just like training wheels and you can choose to use them or not,and you can also choose to have the lines, but have different types, if you want.The npcs aren't perfect shots, but they're not terrible either,and sometimes they'll miss after perfectly shooting 4-ball in a row or something, for example;it's a bit random, kinda like a real person might miss, even if they're good.There's plenty of content to play,challenges in the game that unlock bonus rounds, new areas and npc characters,or reward you with a design for the cue, ball, or table, that you can use to play with.And of course there's still the steam achievements.Or you can try to master the advanced tricks from the tutorial and try them in free mode and then later against npcs.You can also repeat maps you've played already (when you unlock something it gets unlocked for permanent use).Some games I regret buying, but this is definitely not one of them.If you like pool games, this is a nice one to have"
